TOP-SELLING author Jackie Phamotse is releasing another book set to hit the shelves in May titled Bare IV Mercy, that promises to reveal political sex scandals. According to the cover, it’s about the sins of our most powerful leaders, breaking down politicians’ minds and shattering the system. It includes high profile names such as former president Jacob Zuma, former home affairs minister Malusi Gigaba and Police Minister Bheki Cele. On Tuesday, 15 February Jackie announced on Instagram: “Their stories couldn’t die, so we painted them in ink. #Bare4 #BAREMERCY New book reveal.” Her announcement received a warm welcome from industry friends and followers. Actress Shoki Mmola congratulated her and said: “I am so proud of you. New read, new experience. . . something worth celebrating.” ALSO READ | BOITY AND BAE SPILL BEANS Phemelo commented: “Mama, you want to keep us glued again. Your books are super good.” Wendy Makhanya posted: “Oh my Jackie, thank you for showing us something to be looking out for, can it be May already.” Refilwe Merwe said: “I absolutely cannot wait to read this one… Ous Jackie bathong.” BareIV Mercy is the fourth in the Bare series, the others being Bare: The Blesser’s Game, Bare: The Cradle of the Hockey Club and Bare III: Ego. She’s also published Shattered Innocence, I Tweet What I Like…So Sue Me and the children’s book titled Liwa. A post shared by Jackie Phamotse (@jackie_phamotse) 